That he will not. 'Tis your fault, 'tis
your fault;
'tis a good dog.

Ay, sir, you shall find me reasonable;
if it be so,
I shall do that is reason.

Discard, bully Hercules; cashier:
let them wag;
trot, trot.

Bardolph, follow him. A tapster is a

good trade: 
an old cloak makes a new jerkin;

a withered serving-man 
a fresh tapster. Go;

adieu.

By gar, he is de coward Jack priest
of de vorld;
he is not show his face.

It appears so by his weapons. Keep
them asunder;
here comes Doctor Caius. Enter HOST, CAIUS and RUGBY.

Well, heaven knows how I
love you;
and you shall one day find it.

Nay, I must tell you, so you
do;
or else I could not be in that mind.

Pray you, come near: if I suspect
without cause,
why then make sport at me;
then let me be your jest;
I deserve it. How
now! whither bear you this?

By gar, 'tis no the fashion of
France;
it is not jealous in France.

Seese is not good to give putter;
your belly is all
putter.

Vere is Mistress Page? By gar, I
am cozened: I ha'
married un garcon, a boy;
un paysan, by gar, a boy;
it is not Anne
Page: by gar, I am cozened.
